1. There was a preoperative chemotherapy arm in the study.
2. There was a surgery-alone arm in the study.
3. The median survival time (MST) was measured in the study.
4. The MST in the preoperative chemotherapy arm was lower than that of the surgery-alone arm.
5. The MST in the preoperative chemotherapy arm was 45.42 months.
6. The MST in the surgery-alone arm was 57.59 months.
7. The difference in MST between the preoperative chemotherapy arm and the surgery-alone arm was statistically significant with a P-value of 0.016.
